source capacity Works with Resource Management to produce 90 and 180 day CSLA reports and reviews with executive Helps drive, test and refine best practices for all account management services Partners on best practice processes with Communication Services Cross-Functional Collaboration Partners with functional communications to ensure strategy and message alignment Partners with external communications disciplines (PR, AR, IR) to establish/support client strategies for top tier clientsDesired Skills and ExperienceSkill Sets: 5+ years executive communication experience Strategic communications planning and execution - Demonstrates above average understanding and strategic thinking across multiple communication disciplines. Has successfully developed and executed internal and/or external communication plans. Executive presence -  Experience advising /working directly with executives Excellent writing skills Strong Power Point skills Solid ability to create a storyline and develop a messaging platform Strong people and collaborative skills necessary to work effectively across multiple global functions and with varied levels of management Excellent multi-tasking capability and ability to work in a dynamic faced paced environment Strong team player with a positive attitude and strong sense of accountabilityStrong collaborator - Ability to partner across mix of constituents and organizations Virtual Leader - Ability to effectively lead virtual teams in a matrix environment Innovative thinker Customer-focusedAbout this companyChannel ImpactChannel Impact is the leading, full-service channel specialist for technology companies who want to drive incremental sales, at high profit, through best-in-class partnering. We help customers ramp up their sales quickly and increase market share, with high customer satisfaction and low cost of sales. We provide: Services that will enhance your channel strategy Solutions to enable your channel Tools to measure results At Channel Impact,